content.detailedDescription:
My girlfriend and i were sitting in her car in her driveway enjoying the clear night sky through the sun roof.  i was looking up (about 75 degrees off the horizon, and roughly due n-ne) when i noticed a redish light that seemed to fade in to my field of vision between two stars. i immediately thought it was a satellite until it got very bright and began to travel north.  it dimmed down fairly quickly(after 2-2.5 seconds or so), then changed into a light blue color(1-2seconds).  it continued it's motion and faded to black.  

      i said aloud to my girlfriend "what the hell is that thing?", and pointed in the general direction i saw it disappear.  she began to look the right direction as it began to glow red, fade to blue, and disappear again.  we watched it for about a minute before it began to head in a more n-ne direction, always pulsating the same color pattern, but the intervals between it disappearing and reappearing weren't evenly spaced apart.


    we continued to watch it for about 2 minutes, and it seemed to be growing much smaller (although it wasn't relatively big to begin with) until it just seemed to fade to black for good.  we were both slightly shaken from the underlying excitement of seeming an anomaly that we couldn't logically explain away.


we went inside to fetch a video camera just in case, but it did not return after about an hour of watching for it.


it is worth noting that we live under somewhat trafficked airspace (austin bergstrom intl), but when i saw it appear i had a clear view of the sky around the area and it did not seem to fly into my field of vision.  if it had, where it was coming from/where it was headed isn't really facing the airport to the best of my determination.   just kind of faded in.
content.summary: Small red light appeared in sky, grew very bright, dulled, the pulsed red/blue/none while traveling northward

content.detailedDescription:
I have been observing these for several months both in denver and arizona. it is imperative to observe the sky in near dark conditions with minimum of light pollution. these observations invariably involve what looks like stars moving at extremely high speed flying south to north and occasionally north to south. also some have been seen flying sw to ne.
tonight we witnessed these five times in twenty minutes.
then we saw two flying in tandem. the rear on caught up with the front one the suddenly turned 90 degrees and shot off to the east.
by deduction i would estimate their speed to be in excess of 50,000 mph and certainly capable of traveling pole to pole in 20 to 30 minutes.
the point is that we have been observing these for many months and i suggest others participate in observing these.
these are too fast for satellites and were too high for aircraft )there were no anti-collision lights)
please consider asking others to participate in observing these. if we saw five in twenty minutes in just one sector (which implies 300 flights a day!) then this represents a huge amount of activity going on in the upper atmosphere.'
accurate feedback would be appreciated.
content.summary: Extremely high altiude - extremely high speed

content.detailedDescription:
On a summer evening, in as best as i can recall in 1966/67 a group of us were playing in our front yard. we noticed a light off in the distance come down from the sky over the mountains and into a wheat field. it then moved toward us at about 30ft above the wheat tops until it was approximately 300 yds away and stopped. there was a small dry canyon between it and us. we called for my parents, who came outside and also witnessed this object that was now just hovering. it remained stationary for about ten minutes, making no sound at all. it was approximatly 40 ft or a little more in width and approximatly 15 ft in hieght. it had white panels around the circumfrence which were illuminated. the top and bottom of the craft appeared to be light gray.During it's hover many, many other children and adults from the neighborhood gathered in our yard watching it. this included a policeman and several men that worked at the nearby "martin plant".
 
the object then moved off back toward the mountain range gaining speed until it reached the base of the foot hills and then just lifted off at a tremendous rate of speed into space. it did not "tilt" up when it went up. it remained flat and just took off at approximatly a 45% angle over the rocky mountains. it only to it 8 to 10 sec. to completly clear the mountain range.
content.summary: Craft descended over mountains, came straight to us and hovered. then left.

content.detailedDescription: I was looking for more info. on ufo sightings wed., june 6, 2012 around 10:45 p.M. in northcentral indiana.  i was outside and saw a large white ball of light, traveling from southwest to northeast, low in the sky(lower than a jet).  it was a steady light, not blinking, without a trail of light behind it.  there was no sound.  i watched it travel at a steady speed.  that same evening, within about 30 min. we saw several smaller, higher objects traveling from east to west(2), north to south (1), south to north(1) and east to west(1).  the one traveling east to west appeared to dim, then go back to the normal light.  these were as high as i think i have seen satellites orbiting( maybe these were satellites, but it seemed a lot within the 30 min.)  i saw 2 of the higher ones, last night, north to south and south to north about the same time period.  i was in front of my house and at first thought the large object was a headlight of a plane, but there was no blinking lights or sound.  i lost sight of the object as it continued ne.
content.summary: Solid glowing light traveling med.  rate of speed sw-ne; 4 other higher lights traveling different directions; one changed direction & brightened

content.detailedDescription: I was watching television from my couch and decided to make sure all of the doors were locked prior to going to bed. as i stood up i looked at the time on the cable box. it was 11:20 pm. i went downstairs to the den/office to close the patio door that face east. when i got to the door i noticed two objects flying/floating through the air, in tandem, to the east ( rear )  of my house. as far as i could tell both objects were circular, ( the one in the rear may have been somewhat oval in shape but both were about the same size. the one that was in front was glowing white, the one that was following was slightly elevated above the front and was glowing orange. there was no sound from either object. at the same time at a greater distance i could see an airplane flying off in the same direction. ( i live about 40 mins. northwest of  ohare and see airplanes all of the time either transiting in or out.) at first i thought these objects must be airplanes or helicopters but as they came closer the shapes did not bear this out. while i have seen, at times, satellites and a few yrs ago saw the iss and space shuttle fly over, these objects did not look like any of those either. the objects were flying at a normal speed. they did not deviate from their flight path. i thought about reporting this to the local police but did not do so since it was late and did not want to endure any kind of criticism or skepticism from them. i did search for other reports and did not find any for this time or date in this area.
content.summary: I saw two aircraft flying from south to north, neither made any sound, one in the front was white the one that followed was orange

i remember thinking were is our airforce what is this thing in our airspace they can come and go and we can do anything about it. we told our parents but they didnt believe.

content.detailedDescription:
Myself, my wife and a friend visiting from out of town were sitting in our back yard having a cigarette.  my wife noticed on the eastern horizon a cylinder shaped glowing light approaching us and said look what is that?, we looked up and saw the craft approaching, it looked like a large flying wing as its span was pointing north to south as it was flying east to west. the underside was illuminated with a soft glowing bluish/white light all the way around the cylinder shape.  as it crossed the entire sky we could definitely discern the dark gray cylinder shape as it was slightly illuminated by the undercarriage lights, then as it got directly over us it shifted on its axis in a clockwise direction from 45 degrees to 90 degrees, going from a flying wing  type of thing to a flying torpedo or cigar shape would be the best way to describe it, it continued to the west and out over the ocean and disappeared over the horizon.  all of our feelings were that this was like no other craft we have ever seen, and moved in a way that we all know is not physically possibly by our current aviation technology.

we tried to get photos on our cell phones, my wife may have some, mine didnt turn out as it was moving pretty quickly, once we can d/l hers onto the computer i can forward them.  but this was definately a sighting witnessed by 3 of us at one time
content.summary: Cylinder shape ufo traveling east to west that shifted its axis from 45 degrees to 90 degrees during flight

content.detailedDescription:
I went outside to smoke and looked up at the brightest star only to notice odd circular motions and movements that were very fast and turns that were instantaneous. we observed to object and all agreed it was not a terrestrial craft as the movements it made were unlike those we have ever witnessed. the "craft" appeared to move like it was tethered to the ground which was impossible due to the height of the "craft". it circled the same area for an hour or so and then became obscured by cloud cover. google star maps showed no stars in the area and my cell phone camera was compromised by city lights. 
to this day i have never seen anything like it! very very strange!
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: The object made no noise and appeared to be a staar until strange movements were observed. this was seen and confirmed by both my wife and mother.

content.detailedDescription: Approximately 10:55 pm, i had gone outside because our driveway alarm had sounded. as i was looking for the cause, my gaze went immediately to some solidly bright, circular lights moving in an ascending sw direction from very low directly east of me.  initially there was a group of three , then three more, then two, and two.  the last one moved far more slowly and more vertically.  there was virtually no sound.  the orbs seemed to pulsate red and yellow, but mostly yellow and were distinctly constant bright. they did not flash or have any strobe effect.  the distance between the lights varied, and they did not follow any formation pattern, each going in a slightly different direction.  they moved at a rate i would expect of a helicopter, but the rate of ascension and distance covered seemed out of helicopter capability at this altitude.  as bright as the lights were, i expected to see them for some time as they left this large valley, but they disappeared relatively quickly from sight.  i would estimate they covered a distance of 50-60 miles in about 5 minutes relative to the ground.  both my wife and i saw them.  i took pictures with my cell phone, but don't know if they will show anything since i was shooting into a night sky.  i did make sure i got some ground yard night lites for comparison. the closest description i can give of the sight was it looked like a giant version of the firework type that is a cardboard tube held in the hand that shot out a colored ball sporadically i think was called a "cannon ball"?  it was a completely cloudless, clear night.
content.summary: String of 10 red/yellow circular lights moving sw appearing to originate low to ground and rose slowly. distance between lights irregular and irregular travel path

content.detailedDescription: While relaxing on a neighbors porch in may i noticed three red blinking lights ascending closely in the sky.  it was like a maneuver from an air show but there was not sound and they weren't in any obvious formation but they were extremely close.  as i stood up to get a better view i noticed three more similar lights ascending, and still no sound. the lights seemed to meet at a certain point then five lights traveled northwest in a straight path and one continued east without an addition ascent.  it flew in front of me above house level on the next level of houses above my own and then disappeared while traveling east.  right after it happened i though that i must have seen helicopters or small plains but there was no noise, there were too many and they were too close to not hear any noise at all.  i am extremely close to the mountain and every sound echoes, if there was a sound i would have heard it.  my neighbor and i were so happy that we saw it together and we quickly begun to research other similar sightings.  another explanation for what i saw that i found while researching was that i may have saw chinese lanterns.  i didn't dismiss this right away but after looking at all the youtube video i could find on chinese lanterns i have come the conclusion that it was neither that object.  first of all the object moved too quickly and in a straight line at the same latitude.  chinese lanterns ascend...Consistently slowly.  another thing was if it were a lantern and being pushed by wind why did five change direction while one continued in a straight path.
content.summary: Red round blinking lights, no sound, going about as fast as a fast moving helicopter
